    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.7.2\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux on Windows 10 x86_64\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nwindows terminal\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nsystem package manager : pacman\n\n### How to reproduce the issue\n\n### 1. \r\nnvim --clean debug.vim\r\n\r\ndebug.vim:\r\n\r\n```vim\r\n\" This is a vim comment.\r\n```\r\n### 2. For `hi! def link`\r\n\r\n```vim\r\n:hi vimComment\r\nvimComment     xxx links to Comment\r\n\r\n:hi! def link vimComment Boolean\r\n\r\n:hi vimComment\r\nvimComment     xxx links to Boolean\r\n```\r\n\r\n### 3. For `nvim_set_hl`\r\n\r\n```vim\r\n:hi vimComment\r\nvimComment     xxx links to Comment\r\n\r\n:call nvim_set_hl(0, 'vimComment', {'link':'Boolean','default':1})\r\n\r\n:hi vimComment\r\nvimComment     xxx links to Comment\r\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nExpected an options to make `nvim_set_hl` behave the same as `hi! def link`.\n\n### Actual behavior\n\nIf `vimComment` already has highlight, `:hi! def link vimComment Boolean` would override the origin highlight, but `:call nvim_set_hl(0, 'vimComment', {'link':'Boolean','default':1})` can't override it.\r\n",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Note: \r\n\r\nAt least, `hi! def link <name> <value>` could be achieved by using two call to `nvim_set_hl`:\r\n\r\n```lua\r\nvim.api.nvim_set_hl(0, name, {})\r\nvim.api.nvim_set_hl(0, name, { link = value, default = true })\r\n```\r\n\r\nSo this problem may also be solved by documenting `:h nvim_set_hl()`",
