            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "When `<name>` has linked highlight, `nvim_set_hl(0, <name>, {'link':<val>,'default':1})` behave the same as `hi def link <name> <val>`:\r\n```log\r\n1. :hi vimComment\r\nvimComment     xxx links to Comment\r\n2. :hi def link vimComment Boolean\r\n3. :hi vimComment\r\nvimComment     xxx links to Comment\r\n4. :hi clear\r\n5. :hi vimComment\r\nvimComment     xxx links to Comment\r\n\r\n1. :hi vimComment\r\nvimComment     xxx links to Comment\r\n2. :call nvim_set_hl(0, 'vimComment', {'link':'Boolean','default':1})\r\n3. :hi vimComment\r\nvimComment     xxx links to Comment\r\n4. :hi clear\r\n5. :hi vimComment\r\nvimComment     xxx links to Comment\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhen `<name>` has highlight and doesn't have linked highlight, `nvim_set_hl(0, <name>, {'link':<val>,'default':1})` does not link to `val`, which is different from `hi def link <name> <val>`:\r\n\r\n```log\r\n1. :hi abc guifg=#123123\r\n2. :hi def link abc Boolean\r\n3. :hi abc\r\nabc            xxx guifg=#123123\r\n4. :hi clear\r\n5. :hi abc\r\nabc            xxx links to Boolean\r\n\r\n1. :hi abc guifg=#123123\r\n2. :call nvim_set_hl(0, 'abc', {'link':'Boolean','default':1})\r\n3. :hi abc\r\nabc            xxx guifg=#123123\r\n4. :hi clear\r\n5. :hi abc\r\nabc            xxx cleared\r\n```",
